Analyze Your Data with Models and Insights

Create models to analyze your data. Explore the insights that Einstein Discovery revealed in your data using AI, machine learning, and statistical analysis. Insights show you what happened in your data, why it happened, and what could happen.

Create and Manage Models
Models tell Einstein Discovery what to analyze. Creating a model involves defining the dataset fields, outcome variable, explanatory variables, and other settings to include in the analysis.

Explore Data Insights
You can explore insights for any model to which you have access. An insight is a statistically significant finding in your data. When you create a model version, Einstein Discovery analyzes the data in your dataset and generates insights based on its analysis. Insights provide a starting point for you to investigate the relationships among your modelâ€™s explanatory variables and its goal.
title: Einstein Discovery: Analyzing Data with Salesforce Analytics
